revised and new methods are$\backslash$nrobust under nonstandard conditions. But considering the need to catch$\backslash$nan elevation sign ambiguity in the revised method (which cannot be$\backslash$nexcluded to fail in rare instances), the new method is regarded as more$\backslash$nrobust and unproblematic, for example, for applications in radar forward$\backslash$noperators.},
